#eNCA Courtesy #DStv403  JOHANNESBURG - Eskom's unreliable power supply is leading to the shedding of customers. Those who can afford alternatives are disconnecting from the grid. This means the utility is losing much-needed income which could lead to its demise. But, the University of Pretoria's David Walwyn warns this will hurt those with no other means of getting power. Watch the full interview in the video above. 